<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-26T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-26T14:00:00-05:00" n="432" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Italy/170: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Italy (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to">Garrett</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-26T14:00:00-05:00">March
                                        26, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>25. Department’s circular February 26th, 11 A.M. Treasury draft of
                                agreement to carry out Congressional Resolution regarding debt
                                postponement has been handed to Italian Ambassador today. Treasury
                                anxious to expedite action. Department does not desire that you make
                                special call on officials regarding this but in connection with
                                other matters hopes you will find opportunity to inquire whether
                                prompt action can be expected.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>